                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/23: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-05T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 5, 1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received March 5—2:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>306. Following from American Consul General, Mukden: <pb facs="0622" n="518"
                        xml:id="pg_518"/>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“March 4, 5 p.m. <persName corresp="#p_CH3">Chao</persName>, Mayor of
                            Mukden, in a press interview today, stated that <persName
                                corresp="#p_CC4">Chang Ching-hui</persName> would go to Tangkangtze,
                            60 miles south of Mukden on the 7th where he will meet ex-Emperor
                                <persName corresp="#p_PH1">Hsuan-tung</persName> who is to be
                            brought for this purpose from Port Arthur, and make the third request
                            that he ‘resume the post’. <persName corresp="#p_CH3">Chao</persName>
                            stated that it is expected he must accept the proposal and that he will
                            proceed to Changchun where the installation ceremony will take place on
                            the 9th. The 10th, 11th, 12th will be declared holidays throughout the
                            provinces.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
